    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A class of materials used as an alternative to fiber reinforced polymer (FRP) for shear strengthening and seismic retrofitting of concrete structures. A mortar incorporates textile comprised of woven or knitted fiber rovings in two or more, usually orthogonal, directions. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
